 ok‚Üêrun _onResize message;object;tunits;size
‚çù This is often coming from the Configure or StateChange event, so we need to translate

 object‚Üê‚äÉmessage
 size‚Üêobject ‚éïVGET‚äÇ'_size'‚ç¨
 tunits‚Üê‚äÉ_supp.MyUnits object
 :Select 2‚äÉmessage
 :Case 'Configure'
     ‚çù message[3 4]‚ÜêY,X (pixel) position of top-left corner on parent
     ‚çù message[5 6]‚ÜêH,W (pixel) size of object
     ok‚Üê1‚ä£(0,‚ç®message[5 6]√∑tunits)0 ##.Run run
 :Case 'StateChange'
     ‚çù message[3]‚Üê0:Restoring, 1:Minimizing, 2:Maximizing
     ok‚Üê1‚ä£(message[3],‚ç®size√∑tunits)0 ##.Run run
 :Case '' ‚çù Implicit internal call
‚çù? I assume we'll be passing the correct arguments directly?
     ok‚Üêmessage 0 ##.Run run
 :EndSelect
